# 09 — Actor re-entrancy guard (F-01)
# close() arrives between commit and completion handler — state guard drops stale frame.
# Cross-ref: design/03-metal-pipeline.md §onFrameReadbackComplete, review/02-adversarial-red-team.md F-01

shape: sequence_diagram

VM: CameraViewModel
CE: CameraEngine actor
GPU: Metal GPU
CH: "Completion handler\n(Metal internal thread)"

Actor is busy — processFrame(N) in flight: {
  VM -> CE: "await close()\n(queued in mailbox)"
}

processFrame(N) — commit phase: {
  CE -> CE: encode command buffer
  CE -> CE: "frameSessionState = sessionState\n// captured as .streaming"
  CE -> CE: "addCompletedHandler { cb in\n  if cb.status == .error { ... return }\n  Task { await onFrameReadbackComplete(\n    readIndex: i,\n    expectedState: .streaming)\n  }\n}"
  CE -> CE: commandBuffer.commit()
  CE -> CE: writeIndex = 1 - writeIndex
  CE -> CE: "processFrame(N) returns"
}

close() runs (mailbox pumps): {
  CE -> CE: "gpuStallWatchdogTask.cancel()"
  CE -> CE: "retryTask?.cancel()"
  CE -> CE: "sessionState = .closed"
  CE -> CE: "releaseMetalResources()\n// readbackBuffers freed"
  CE -> CE: session.stopRunning()
  CE -> VM: return
}

GPU is still executing frame N: {
  GPU -> CH: command buffer complete (async)
  CH -> CE: "Task { await onFrameReadbackComplete(readIndex, expectedState: .streaming) }"
}

Guard catches state mismatch — frame dropped: {
  CE -> CE: "guard sessionState == expectedState\nsessionState == .closed\nexpectedState == .streaming\n⇒ guard FAILS"
  CE -> CE: "return — frame dropped\n(readback buffer was freed)"
}
